# Screens and database

## Screens (`src/screens/`)

- Keep screen containers thin; put data/effects in **`use*Screen.ts`** next to the screen when that pattern exists in the folder.
- Colocate **`styles.ts`** and **`components/`** with the screen when neighboring files already use that layout.
- Use `@/` imports; avoid deep relative `../../../` when an alias fits.

## Database (`src/lib/database/`)

- One concern per module (e.g. `users.ts`, `checkIns.ts`); aggregate exports in **`index.ts`** for shared entrypoints.
- Reuse **`types.ts`** and existing ID/session patterns; do not bypass auth/session assumptions without an explicit product reason.

```typescript
// Prefer
import { something } from '@/lib/database';

// Avoid duplicating raw client setup outside `appwrite.ts` / established patterns
```
